  "description": [
    "By LOWNDES MAURY My information comes from an educated Korean living in Butte He lived in Korea until early manhood He has no leaning toward Commu nism in fact is a personal friend of Syngham Rhee president of South Korea He spent several months in South Korea last year He tells me that Fortyfive per cent of the South Koreans lean toward Communism also that all Koreans hope to see their country united also that all Koreans object to the presence of both Rus sians and Americans in Korea the Koreans wish to be let alone Korea the peninsular of Chosen is about the size of Idaho or one half the size of California It is now cut in about two equal paxts The population is estimated at 24 million The climate is mild Seoul and San Fxancisco axe of the same latitude 38 degrees North Koiea has mines developed water power timber South Korea is mostly farming land American capital is invested in Korea Our concern about Korea may be mostly to protect this Just as our concern about South East Asia is to secure the present channels of natuial iubber to mix with our synthetic It is probable"
  ],
